ZH: 农民每天都要出去耕田。
EN: Farmers have to go out to plow the fields every day.

ZH: 爷爷用牛耕地，现在我们用机器。
EN: Grandpa used oxen to plow the land, now we use machines.

ZH: 耕地的时候要先锄草。
EN: When plowing the land, you need to weed first.

ZH: 现代农业已经不再依赖手工耕作。
EN: Modern agriculture no longer relies on manual plowing.

ZH: 他们昨天整天都在田里耕地。
EN: They were plowing the fields all day yesterday.

ZH: 耕土时要保持一定的速度。
EN: Maintain a certain speed when plowing the soil.

ZH: 他很享受在田野中耕作的时光。
EN: He enjoys the time spent plowing in the fields.

ZH: 大雨过后，一片片田地需要重新耕耘。
EN: After the heavy rain, the fields need to be plowed again.

ZH: 耕作是农村人最常做的活儿。
EN: Plowing is the most common activity for rural people.

ZH: 这块地需要今天就耕好。
EN: This piece of land needs to be plowed today.

ZH: 农民们开始耕地，为下一季的收成做准备。
EN: Farmers start plowing the land to prepare for the next season's harvest.

ZH: 地主自己不肯动手，总是让佃户来耕地。
EN: The landlord never does the plowing himself, always asking the tenant farmers to do it.

ZH: 耕地耕心情，爱心爱生活。
EN: Plow the land, plow the mood, love life.

ZH: 大家一起耕作，劳动成果分根据劳力分配。
EN: Everyone works together, and the results are distributed according to the labor.

ZH: 春耕秋收是农村传统的生产方式。
EN: Spring plowing and autumn harvest is a traditional way of production in the countryside.

ZH: 耕地不容易，需要有耐心和毅力。
EN: Plowing the land is not easy, it requires patience and perseverance.

ZH: 农民为了收获都会逢春就耕地了。
EN: Farmers will plow the land in spring in order to harvest.

ZH: 耕作时候别想太多，把精力集中在手上。
EN: Don't think too much when plowing, focus your energy on your hands.

ZH: 耕作不只是一种劳作，也是一种乐趣。
EN: Plowing is not just a kind of labor, it is also a kind of fun.

ZH: 昔日村庄的风景，在我们的记忆里叫做“耕耘”。
EN: The scenery of the ancient village is called "plowing" in our memory.
